appache-httdp:

1.Download appache-httpd (2.4.41)

	1.1  ./configure
		Error faced:
			apr installed
			sudo apt-get install libpcre3-dev
	1.2 make
        1.3 sudo make install

Note: apache2 directory is created in /urs/local


2. Download mod_cluster
	2.1 I have downloaded 1.3.1 version (but it old now)
	2.2 Need to generate the .so file from mod_cluster and that modules need to add to apache2/modules/
		2.2.1-->/mod_cluster1.3.1/native/   

create .so file for mensioned modules: advertise,mod_cluster_slotmem,mod_manager,mod_proxy_cluster/


3.Advertise:

	3.1cd advertise
	3.2 sudo apt-get install autoconf     --->(install if not installed)-->Need to run ./buildconf   file which give configure file
	3.3  ./configure --with-apxs=/usr/local/apache2/bin/apxs
        3.4  sudo make   ---> .so file will generate   (mod_advertise.so will create)
        3.5 copy generated .so file to /usr/local/apache2/modules             -->(sudo cp -r *.so /usr/local/apache2/modules/)

4.mod_cluster_slotmem

        4.1 cd mod_cluster_slotmem
	4.2 ./buildconf
	4.3  ./configure --with-apxs=/usr/local/apache2/bin/apxs
	4.4 sudo make
	4.5 sudo cp -r *.so /usr/local/apache2/modules/

5.mod_manager
	5.1 cd mod_manager
	5.2 ./buildconf
	5.3  ./configure --with-apxs=/usr/local/apache2/bin/apxs
	5.4 sudo make
	5.5 sudo cp -r *.so /usr/local/apache2/modules/

6.mod_proxy_cluster

	6.1 cd mod_proxy_cluster
	6.2 ./buildconf
	6.3  ./configure --with-apxs=/usr/local/apache2/bin/apxs
	6.4 sudo make
	6.5 sudo cp -r *.so /usr/local/apache2/modules/


7.Now we need to load the module which we copied(.so) to /module directory --->Distination: /usr/local/apach2/conf/httpd.conf


ADD this to httpd.conf:


LoadModule advertise_modules modules/mod_advertise.so
LoadModule manager_module modules/mod_manager.so
LoadModule proxy_cluster_module modules/mod_proxy_cluster.so
LoadModule cluster_slotmem_module modules/mod_cluster_slotmem.so





<IfModule manager_module>
	Listen 127.0.0.1:10001
	ManagerBalancerName ctbs-utility
<VirtualHost 127.0.0.1:10001>
	<Location />
		Require all granted
	</Location>
	<Location /mod_cluster-manager>
		SetHandler mod_cluster-manager
		Require all granted
	</Location>
</VirtualHost>
</IfModule>

	Note: remove # in mod_proxy.os and mod_proxy_ajp.so



8.start the httpd

/usr/local/apache2/bin/
	sudo ./apachectl
		check the process like:  ps -ef|grep httpd


Now check on browser:http://localhost:80    -->for httpd
Now check for mod_cluster:  http://localhost:10001//mod_cluster-manager            -->port and name given in httpd.conf file









	






 



 
